How can you fall in love when you can’t even hold hands? Due to a childhood curse, anything that the Duke touches will die—which makes his flirty maid’s behavior all the more shocking! Is there a way for the Duke and his companions to somehow break the curse, or is he doomed to a life where love is forever out of his reach?
(Source: Funimation)
Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu 3rd Season
Action, Adventure, Drama, Fantasy, Psychological, Romance, Thriller

The third season of Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu. A year has passed since Subaru’s victory at the Sanctuary. He savors a life of fulfillment while Emilia’s camp stands united for the royal selection—until a fateful letter arrives. Anastasia, a royal selection candidate, has invited Emilia to the Watergate City of Priestella. But as the party begins its journey, crisis stirs beneath the surface and Subaru meets a cruel fate once again. (Source: Crunchyroll) Notes: The first episode has an extended runtime of ~90 minutes, and received an early premiere at Anime Expo on July 5, 2024.
Akuyaku Reijou desu ga, Shiawase ni Natte Misemasu wa!

Annuled engagements, "serves you right"s, condemnation events, doting, royalty, reincarnated heroines, banishment endings... it's fully loaded with all the charms of villainesses!! Despite all the Villainess' stories starting off in dire straits, in the end they're...all happy endings♪ A comicalization of popular villainess stories that were published on Shousetsuka ni Narou! An anthology of oneshots with happy endings!! Volume 1 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "The Villainess Will Obtain True Love" by Hoshino Soumei Author: Nekomata Doremi An annulled engagement at a graduation party?! 2. "The Tale of the Noble Girl who will go to a Monastery after her Engagement Annulment" by Sorakura SHIJIKI, Author: Yuuki Satoru Banishment after her younger sister steals her fiance?! 3. "I Will Definitely Get My Engagement Annulled! ~I will become a Villainess!" by Kuroe Yui, Author: Reiga Utsuho To break off her engagement, she harasses the daughter of a Baron?! 4. "Shall We Walk Hand in Hand Down the Flowery Path of Evil?" by Yamashiro Umeta, Author: Mafuyubi After her engagement is annulled, she gets married to a fat old baldy?! 5. "The Villainess Trifles with the Second Prince's First Love" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Mizuno Saaya After being condemned, the second prince appears before me... Volume 2 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "It's Been 10 Years Since You Asked to Break Off Our Engagement, If You Insist That Much, Let's Break It Off!" by Maro, Author: Yoshimura She's been told multiple times since they were young to break off the engagement?! 2. "The Villainess Laughs Innocently" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Yoruru A Condemnation Event after being called out to the rear garden?! 3. "The Art of Rebuilding a Nation Begins with a Broken Engagement!" by Kawano Akiko, Author: Hazuki The Prince has an affair with the Saintess and calls off his engagement?! 4. "You Were Set Up, You Know?" by Koyuki Iroha, Author: Yuki Yukiko At the graduation party, my older sister's engagement was broken?! 5. Come Quickly, my Engagement Breaking Event" by Mochida Moo, Author: Kyouka The only ally the reincarnated Villainess has is the butler?!

How do you use Aeron MDS with multiple publishers and a single subscriber where the publishers are unaware of the subscriber machine IPs?

I am trying to use Aeron Multi-Destination-Subscriptions where I have multiple publishers publish messages to their own IP address and port. I want a subscriber to subscribe to each of the publishers IP addresses and PORTs on the same stream ID. The publishers and subscribers are on separate machines. For simplicity, I'm testing this with a single Publisher and Subscriber setup. I am using docker to create a virtual network so I can designate the IPs of the publisher and subscriber machines. Here is my example code: Publication code final String publicationChannel = new ChannelUriStringBuilder() .media(UDP_MEDIA) (3 more lines were trimmed) Subscription code final String subscriptionChannel = new ChannelUriStringBuilder() .media(UDP_MEDIA) (8 more lines were trimmed) I have a doWork in both of these which repeatedly call subscription.isConnected() and publication.isConnected(). I expected this to work just like the MDC example where you can use control-mode=manual on the publication side and call publication.addDestination(subscriberIP:port) where the subscription would be setup to subscribe to its own subscriberIP:port. In testing, the publication and subscription are not connected. This test class in the aeron repo uses MDS over UDP using localhost and using multicast addresses MDSTest so I thought the same would hold true for using the publisher machines IP and port. Would really appreciate if someone could explain why this doesn't work?
